<title>USA: BFGoodrich to sell Tremco unit to RPM.</title>
<headline>BFGoodrich to sell Tremco unit to RPM.</headline>
<dateline>AKRON, Ohio 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>BFGoodrich Co said Tuesday that it has an agreement with RPM Inc for RPM to acquire Tremco Inc, a BFGoodrich subsidiary that manufactures and sells sealants and coatings.</p>
<p>The purchase price was not disclosed.</p>
<p>Goodrich said it expects to realize a gain on the sale, which it expects to complete early in the first quarter of 1997.</p>
<p>The company said that the sale of Tremco, which had sales of about $350 million in 1995, will allow Goodrich to accelerate expansion of its core specialty chemicals and aerospace businesses.</p>
</text>
